Pierogi / Varenyky Dough

Canadian measurements • For one batch

Ingredients

• 3 cups all-purpose flour
• 1 tsp fine salt
• 1 large egg, room temperature
• ¾ cup warm water (about 35–40 °C)
• 2 tbsp neutral oil (canola or sunflower)

⸻

Method

Mix
Combine flour and salt in a bowl. Make a well. Add egg, warm water, and oil. Mix with a fork or fingers until a shaggy dough forms and no dry flour remains.

Knead
Turn out onto an unfloured work surface. Knead 6–8 minutes until the dough is smooth, elastic, and supple. The surface should be satiny; the dough should feel soft but not sticky.

If the dough feels dry, add water by the teaspoon during kneading. If slightly tacky, dust minimally with flour. Do not over-flour.

Rest
Form into a tight ball. Wrap completely airtight and rest at room temperature for 30 minutes minimum (up to 60 minutes is acceptable).

⸻

Target Texture

Smooth, extensible, and relaxed. Rolls thin without snap-back or tearing.

⸻

Rolling Guidance

Roll to 1–1.5 mm thickness. Thinner is preferable to thicker. Dough should stretch easily without shrinking.

⸻

Chef Control Notes (non-negotiable)

• Resting is mandatory; skipping it guarantees shrinkage and thick seams.
• Oil moderates gluten strength and improves sealing—do not omit.
• Excess bench flour weakens seals; use only what is required.
• Dough should be neutral in flavour and resilient in handling.
